### TITLE ###
RequiredEnumSelect
### DESCRIPTION ###
-i prompts a required enum arg via a Select. The chosen value lands in the
equivalent invocation printed to stderr, and the script runs with it.
### INPUT ###
args:
    env str # Environment to deploy to.
    env enum ["dev", "staging", "prod"]
print("env={env}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
down
enter
### STDOUT ###
env=staging

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never --env staging

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--env: Environment to deploy to.
> dev
  staging
  prod
--- frame 1 (down) ---
--env: Environment to deploy to.
  dev
> staging
  prod
--- frame 2 (enter) ---
--env staging
### TITLE ###
BoolAnswerYesDefaultFalse
### DESCRIPTION ###
A bool arg prompts y/n with the default capitalized. Answering "y" against a
false default emits --force; the equivalent invocation shows it.
### INPUT ###
args:
    force bool # Skip confirmation.
print("force={force}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
"y"
enter
### STDOUT ###
force=true

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never --force

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--force: Skip confirmation. [y/N]
> █
--- frame 1 (y) ---
--force: Skip confirmation. [y/N]
> y█
--- frame 2 (enter) ---
--force yes
### TITLE ###
BoolAnswerNoDefaultTrue
### DESCRIPTION ###
Answering "n" against a true default emits --cache=false, the only form that
can flip a defaulted-true bool off.
### INPUT ###
args:
    cache bool = true # Use the cache.
print("cache={cache}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
"n"
enter
### STDOUT ###
cache=false

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never --cache=false

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--cache: Use the cache. [Y/n]
> █
--- frame 1 (n) ---
--cache: Use the cache. [Y/n]
> n█
--- frame 2 (enter) ---
--cache no
### TITLE ###
BoolEnterKeepsDefault
### DESCRIPTION ###
Enter on a bool prompt keeps the default and emits no token, keeping the
equivalent invocation minimal.
### INPUT ###
args:
    force bool # Skip confirmation.
print("force={force}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
enter
### STDOUT ###
force=false

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--force: Skip confirmation. [y/N]
> █
--- frame 1 (enter) ---
--force (default: no)
### TITLE ###
IntRangeRevalidation
### DESCRIPTION ###
An int arg validates inline: a value outside the range blocks Enter and renders
the error under the field; editing clears it and a valid value submits.
### INPUT ###
args:
    replicas int # Number of replicas.
    replicas range [1, 10]
print("replicas={replicas}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
"99"
enter
backspace
enter
### STDOUT ###
replicas=9

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never --replicas 9

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--replicas: Number of replicas.
> █
--- frame 1 (9) ---
--replicas: Number of replicas.
> 9█
--- frame 2 (9) ---
--replicas: Number of replicas.
> 99█
--- frame 3 (enter) ---
--replicas: Number of replicas.
> 99█
must be in range [1, 10]
--- frame 4 (backspace) ---
--replicas: Number of replicas.
> 9█
--- frame 5 (enter) ---
--replicas 9
### TITLE ###
RegexRevalidation
### DESCRIPTION ###
A regex-constrained str validates inline on submit.
### INPUT ###
args:
    name str
    name regex "[a-z]+"
print("name={name}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
"7"
enter
backspace
"bob"
enter
### STDOUT ###
name=bob

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never --name bob

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--name
> █
--- frame 1 (7) ---
--name
> 7█
--- frame 2 (enter) ---
--name
> 7█
must match regex: [a-z]+
--- frame 3 (backspace) ---
--name
> █
--- frame 4 (b) ---
--name
> b█
--- frame 5 (o) ---
--name
> bo█
--- frame 6 (b) ---
--name
> bob█
--- frame 7 (enter) ---
--name bob
### TITLE ###
OptionalInputSkippedOnEnter
### DESCRIPTION ###
Enter on an empty optional input means "use the default": no token is emitted
and the final parse applies the default.
### INPUT ###
args:
    replicas int = 3 # Number of replicas.
print("replicas={replicas}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
enter
### STDOUT ###
replicas=3

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--replicas: Number of replicas.
> █Default: 3
--- frame 1 (enter) ---
--replicas (skip - default: 3)
### TITLE ###
OptionalEnumSkipRow
### DESCRIPTION ###
An optional enum gets a synthetic skip row prepended; selecting it emits no
token, so the default applies.
### INPUT ###
args:
    env str = "dev" # Environment to deploy to.
    env enum ["dev", "staging", "prod"]
print("env={env}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
enter
### STDOUT ###
env=dev

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--env: Environment to deploy to.
> (skip - use default: dev)
  dev
  staging
  prod
--- frame 1 (enter) ---
--env (skip - default: dev)
### TITLE ###
CommandPickCascade
### DESCRIPTION ###
With command blocks and no command on the CLI, -i first Selects the command,
then prompts its args. The command token leads the equivalent invocation.
### INPUT ###
command greet:
    name str # Who to greet.
    calls fn():
        print("Hello {name}")

command status:
    code int
    calls fn():
        print("Status {code}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
down
enter
"7"
enter
### STDOUT ###
Status 7

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase status --color=never --code 7

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
Choose a command
> greet
  status
--- frame 1 (down) ---
Choose a command
  greet
> status
--- frame 2 (enter) ---
Command: status
--- frame 3 (initial) ---
--code
> █
--- frame 4 (7) ---
--code
> 7█
--- frame 5 (enter) ---
--code 7
### TITLE ###
PartialCliArgsOnlyMissingPrompted
### DESCRIPTION ###
Args already supplied on the CLI (here positionally) are not re-prompted; -i
composes with partial invocations.
### INPUT ###
args:
    first str
    second str
print("{first} {second}")
### ARGS ###
-i
alpha
### KEYS ###
"beta"
enter
### STDOUT ###
alpha beta

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase alpha --color=never --second beta

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--second
> █
--- frame 1 (b) ---
--second
> b█
--- frame 2 (e) ---
--second
> be█
--- frame 3 (t) ---
--second
> bet█
--- frame 4 (a) ---
--second
> beta█
--- frame 5 (enter) ---
--second beta
### TITLE ###
VariadicOnePerLine
### DESCRIPTION ###
Variadic args prompt one value per line until an empty line, encoded greedily
(--files a b) in the equivalent invocation - the form Ra parses for variadics.
### INPUT ###
args:
    *files str # Files to process.
print(files)
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
"a.txt"
enter
"b 2.txt"
enter
enter
### STDOUT ###
[ "a.txt", "b 2.txt" ]

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never --files a.txt 'b 2.txt'

