--nums (one per line, empty line to finish)
> 3█
--- frame 6 (enter) ---
--nums 3
--- frame 7 (initial) ---
--nums (one per line, empty line to finish)
> █
### TITLE ###
CancelExitsCleanly
### DESCRIPTION ###
Ctrl-C during the walk aborts the run with a clear message and exit code 1.
### INPUT ###
args:
    name str
print("name={name}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
ctrl-c
### STDERR ###
Interactive mode canceled

### FRAMES ###
--- frame 0 (initial) ---
--name
> █
### EXIT ###
1
### TITLE ###
NoArgsDeclaredJustRuns
### DESCRIPTION ###
-i on a script with no args prompts nothing, prints the equivalent invocation,
and runs.
### INPUT ###
print("ran")
### ARGS ###
-i
### STDOUT ###
ran

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never

### TITLE ###
EquivalentInvocationQuoting
### DESCRIPTION ###
Values needing shell quoting are single-quoted in the equivalent invocation, so
it is paste-safe.
