### TITLE ###
BoolsGroupIntoMultipick
### DESCRIPTION ###
Two or more unsupplied bools collapse into one multiselect at the first bool's
position: toggled = true, untoggled = false, defaults preselected. Tokens are
emitted only where the result differs from the default. Here build is toggled
on, cache (default true, preselected) is toggled off, lint is left alone.
### INPUT ###
args:
    name str # Your name.
    build bool # Build the project.
    lint bool # Run linter.
    cache bool = true # Use the cache.
print("name={name} build={build} lint={lint} cache={cache}")
### ARGS ###
-i
### KEYS ###
"bob"
enter
space
down
down
space
enter
### STDOUT ###
name=bob build=true lint=false cache=false

### STDERR ###
Equivalent: rad TestCase --color=never --name bob --build --cache=false

